Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> expr
Rule 1     expr -> expr PLUS term
Rule 2     expr -> term
Rule 3     term -> term MUL NUM
Rule 4     term -> NUM

Terminals, with rules where they appear

MUL                  : 3
NUM                  : 3 4
PLUS                 : 1
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

expr                 : 1 0
term                 : 1 2 3

Parsing method: LALR

state 0

    (0) S' -> . expr
    (1) expr -> . expr PLUS term
    (2) expr -> . term
    (3) term -> . term MUL NUM
    (4) term -> . NUM

    NUM             shift and go to state 3

    expr                           shift and go to state 1
    term                           shift and go to state 2

state 1

    (0) S' -> expr .
    (1) expr -> expr . PLUS term

    PLUS            shift and go to state 4


state 2

    (2) expr -> term .
    (3) term -> term . MUL NUM

    PLUS            reduce using rule 2 (expr -> term .)
    $end            reduce using rule 2 (expr -> term .)
    MUL             shift and go to state 5


state 3

    (4) term -> NUM .

    MUL             reduce using rule 4 (term -> NUM .)
    PLUS            reduce using rule 4 (term -> NUM .)
    $end            reduce using rule 4 (term -> NUM .)


state 4

    (1) expr -> expr PLUS . term
    (3) term -> . term MUL NUM
    (4) term -> . NUM

    NUM             shift and go to state 3

    term                           shift and go to state 6

state 5

    (3) term -> term MUL . NUM

    NUM             shift and go to state 7


state 6

    (1) expr -> expr PLUS term .
    (3) term -> term . MUL NUM

    PLUS            reduce using rule 1 (expr -> expr PLUS term .)
    $end            reduce using rule 1 (expr -> expr PLUS term .)
    MUL             shift and go to state 5


state 7

    (3) term -> term MUL NUM .

    MUL             reduce using rule 3 (term -> term MUL NUM .)
    PLUS            reduce using rule 3 (term -> term MUL NUM .)
    $end            reduce using rule 3 (term -> term MUL NUM .)

